The paper proposes a framework for transfer learning in a distributed network, which involves multiple tasks and nodes. The focus is on improving classification accuracy and privacy while reducing the risks of target tasks. This work involves machine learning, optimization, and distributed systems, which are relevant to several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper deals with transfer learning and support vector machines. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also relevant as the paper proposes a framework for multi-task learning. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with a distributed network. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a consensus-based approach for learning. Finally, cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with a multi-agent learning framework.
